<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Buying too many tools.</strong> Most beginners do not need more equipment — they need fewer decisions.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Choosing difficult crops.</strong> Slow or fussy vegetables create early frustration instead of quick wins.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Overcomplicating the setup.</strong> The best first season is usually simple and focused, not optimized.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most People Should Actually Gift</h2>

  <p>
    Start with a simple seed collection or a beginner-friendly planner. These are the gifts most likely to help someone actually begin and stick with it through the first season.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    The best gift makes starting feel easy.
  </p>
</section>

